{"build_type":"executable","description":"Worker thread body (a spawn entry, parameterless). Reads the shared multi-thread state pointer from global g_mt_shared, atomically claims an index (0 or 1) via fetch-add on the claim counter at shared slot 0, then reads its n (slot 1+idx) and its pre-allocated scheduler buffer pointer (slot 3+idx). It runs the proven single-threaded cooperative fiber scheduler ENTIRELY inside that buffer (zero global-arena allocation, so no cross-thread arena race), computing sum(n). It records its result (slot 5+idx), its OS thread id from gettid (slot 7+idx), and finally sets its done flag (slot 9+idx) last so the core sees done only after result and tid are written (x86 TSO store ordering).","module_name":"worker-thread-executes-claimed-summation-recording-outcome","package_name":"worker-thread-executes-claimed-summation-recording-outcome","function_definitions":{"worker-thread-executes-claimed-summation-recording-outcome":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"seven","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"nine","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":9},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"negone","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"litera